{
  "analysis": "CMake is configured and the library has been partially ported to Linux with Windows shims and case fixes. The converter is failing to compile because we have been guessing legacy struct field names. We have now identified correct definitions in mdftypes.h for several key types: MdfHeader (cId, nMeshCount, nAnimCount, nTextureCount, nByteAlignment, nTotalDataSize), TMdfAnimation (hMeshId, nNumTimelines, fTimeLength, union uTls with TMdfTimeline* pTimeline), TMdfTimeline (nKeyFrames, union uKfs with TMdfKeyframe* pKeyframes), TMdfKeyframe (fKeyTime, vecTranslation, qRotation, vecScale), TMdfVertSta (pos, normal, texcoord), TMdfVertSkn (pos, weights[3], bones[4], normal, texcoord). We still need TMdfMesh and the vertex/indices unions names (UVerts_t, UIdxs_t) to serialize meshes. We should use the public getters in MdfFormat.h (GetHeader, GetMesh, GetAnimation) and header-provided counts to avoid relying on protected members. The next actions: print TMdfMesh, UVerts_t, UIdxs_t definitions to get exact member names; then update converter/main.cpp to the correct fields: header fields, animation fields (including a.uTls.pTimeline and a.fTimeLength), timeline keyframes via tl.uKfs.pKeyframes, vertices (pos/normal/texcoord, weights/bones), indices via m->uIdxs.pIndices (16-bit), bindPose via m->uBnd.pBindMats, parentInfo via m->uPrnt.pParentInfo. After corrections, rebuild and run the converter to produce JSON outputs.",
  "plan": "1) Print TMdfMesh definition and the unions UVerts_t (vertex pointer members) and UIdxs_t (indices pointer members) from mdftypes.h to know the exact names (e.g., uVerts.pVerts or separate pSta/pSkn; uIdxs.pIndices).
2) Rewrite converter/main.cpp to use MdfFormat::GetHeader, GetMesh, GetAnimation and header counts to iterate.
3) Update converter to read animations via a.uTls.pTimeline, timelines via tl.uKfs.pKeyframes, and keyframe fields fKeyTime, vecTranslation, qRotation, vecScale.
4) Serialize meshes: choose vertex type based on mesh.meshType (MESH_STATIC vs MESH_SKINNED), cast uVerts to TMdfVertSta/TMdfVertSkn accordingly, serialize indices from uIdxs.pIndices (16-bit), bindPose from uBnd.pBindMats as 16 floats, parentInfo from uPrnt.pParentInfo, textureIndex from hTexture.
5) Rebuild with cmake and fix any remaining name mismatches.
6) Run the converter on all models in /app/MdfLib/test_models and list outputs in /app/converted_models.",
